{{Metaphor
|Aliases={{Metaphor.Alias
|Metaphor.Alias.Name=PURITY IS CLEANLINESS
|Metaphor.Alias.Provenance=Metaphors We Live By, Philosophy in the Flesh
|Metaphor.Alias.Page no=307
}}{{Metaphor.Alias
|Metaphor.Alias.Name=PURE IS CLEAN
|Metaphor.Alias.Provenance=Elise
}}
|Comments=Note that this metaphor itself doesn't suggest anything regarding good/bad; there can be "pure evil." See related metaphors MORALITY IS PURITY and MORALITY IS CLEANLINESS for the full cascade of good, pure, and clean.
|Tags=purity
|Family=Purity Metaphors, Primary Metaphors, 
|Metaphor Level=General
|Metaphor Type=Primary
|Experiential basis=Pure substances have nothing else mixed in with them; a common impurity is dirt, which is dirty. Hence, impure substances are dirty, and pure substances are clean.
|Source frame=Cleanliness
|Target frame=Purity
|Mappings={{Mapping
|Target=pure_substance
|Source=clean_substance
|Comment=a pure substance is one that is free from other substances (impurities); a clean substance has no dirty or unhealthy substances in it.
}}
|Related metaphors={{Related metaphor
|Related metaphor.Relation type=is related to
|Related metaphor.Name=MORALITY IS PURITY
|Related metaphor.Description=Part of the Purity cascade
}}
|Entailments={{Entailment
|Entailment.Target entailment=Purifying
|Entailment.Source inference=Cleansing
|Entailment.Entailed metaphors=PURIFYING IS CLEANSING
}}
|Examples={{Example
|Example.Language=English
|Example.Text=He's pure evil.
|Example.Provenance=Philosophy in the Flesh (307)
|Example.Comments=pure - target language
}}{{Example
|Example.Text=Her soul was scrubbed clean of impurities.
|Example.Comments=scrubbed clean - source; impurities - target
}}
|Entered by=Elise,
|Status=in development
|Investigated for=English
|Relevant LUs=
}}

