{{Metaphor
|Aliases=
|Comments=Cultural scope checked for Persian--Aria
|Family=Governance metaphors, Primary Metaphors, 
|Metaphor Level=General
|Metaphor Type=Primary
|Cultural scope=American English, Persian
|Source frame=Bounded region
|Target frame=Control
|Mappings={{Mapping
|Target=scope_of_control
|Source=proximal region
}}{{Mapping
|Target=controlling_entity
|Source=center
}}
|Related metaphors={{Related metaphor
|Related metaphor.Relation type=is related to
|Related metaphor.Name=STATES ARE LOCATIONS
}}
|Entailments={{Entailment
|Entailment.Target entailment=The actions of an entity that is within the controlling_entity's scope_of_control can be controlled by that controlling_entity
|Entailment.Source inference=An entity located within the proximal region is proximal to the center (and therefore is likely to be accessible from the center)
}}{{Entailment
|Entailment.Target entailment=The actions of an entity that is not within a controlling_entity's scope_of_control are not controlled by that controlling_entity
|Entailment.Source inference=an entity located in the distal_region is distal from the center (and therefore not likely to be accessible from the center)
}}
|Examples={{Example
|Example.Text=His actions are beyond my control.
|Example.Provenance=Ellen
}}{{Example
|Example.Text=The whole situation spiraled out of (our) control.
|Example.Provenance=Ellen
}}{{Example
|Example.Text=He returned to power.
}}{{Example
|Example.Language=English
|Example.Text=The president is in control of the executive branch.
|Example.Comments=the 'scope of control' /proximal region in this case is defined relative to the dependent entity (the executive branch).
}}{{Example
|Example.Language=English
|Example.Text=President Mubarak has stepped down from power.
|Example.Comments=this example also uses CONTROL IS UP
}}
|Entered by=Ellen
|Last reviewed by=Mark
|Status=in development
|LinkPersian=کنترل کردن منطقه محدود است
|LinkRussian=КОНТРОЛЬ – ЭТО ОГРАНИЧЕННАЯ ОБЛАСТЬ
}}

{{Metaphor
|Aliases={{Metaphor.Alias
|Metaphor.Alias.Name=CONTROL IS UP
}}{{Metaphor.Alias
|Metaphor.Alias.Name=BEING IN CONTROL IS BEING ABOVE
|Metaphor.Alias.Provenance=Grady (1998)
|Metaphor.Alias.Page no=290
}}
|Comments=This entry is the entry for the entailed metaphor CONTROL IS UP, a scalar entailment of CONTROL IS VERTICALITY. The word 'control' in CONTROL IS UP picks out one end of the scale, while the word 'control' in CONTROL IS VERTICALITY is a term covering the entire scale ranging from 'having control over' to 'being subject to control'. For the latter generic metaphor please see its own separate entry under 'related metaphors' below.
|Tags=orientational,
|Family=Grady Primary Metaphors, Orientational Metaphors, 
|Metaphor Level=General
|Metaphor Type=Primary, Entailed
|Source frame=Verticality
|Target frame=Control
|Mappings={{Mapping
|Target=controlling_entity
|Source=higher_positioned_entity
}}
|Related metaphors={{Related metaphor
|Related metaphor.Relation type=is an entailment of
|Related metaphor.Name=CONTROL IS VERTICALITY
}}
|Entailments=
|Examples={{Example
|Example.Language=English
|Example.Text=I am on top of the situation.
}}{{Example
|Example.Language=English
|Example.Text=He's in a superior position.
}}{{Example
|Example.Language=English
|Example.Text=He's in the high command.
}}{{Example
|Example.Language=English
|Example.Text=He's in the upper echelon.
}}{{Example
|Example.Language=English
|Example.Text=His power rose.
}}
|Entered by=Oana,
|Status=in development
|Investigated for=English
|Relevant LUs=
}}

